Fig. 8
 shows the N2 adsorption–desorption isotherm and pore size distribution of BiOIO3-0 and BiOIO3-2. The nitrogen absorption desorption curves (Fig. 8a) of both samples accord with type IV isotherm. The H3 hysteresis loop can be seen in the range of 0.8–1.0 (P/P0
), which proved that the addition of CTAB hardly affects the direct ordered pore structure of BiOIO3-0. Therefore, it can be inferred that both materials have relatively small mesoporous structures. After that, the hysteresis loop extends higher, indicating that there are still macropores exist in the samples. As can be seen from Fig. 8b, there are main peaks at 27 nm, 43 nm, 54 nm respectively, which indicates that there are mesoporous structures (10–50 nm) and macroporous structures (larger than 50 nm) in BiOIO3-0. Correspondingly, the addition of CTAB increased the distribution of pore structure in BiOIO3-2, most of which are pore structures at 68 nm.
